  "grammarPoint": {
    "title": "Time of day, and your first -ся verbs",
    "explanation": "**У́тром, днём, ве́чером, но́чью** — \"in the morning/afternoon/evening/at night\" — are fixed adverb forms. Just learn them as chunks for now.\n\nSome verbs end in **-ся** (просыпа́ться — to wake (oneself) up). They conjugate exactly like normal verbs, you just keep **-ся** (after a consonant) or **-сь** (after a vowel) stuck on the end: **я просыпа́юсь, ты просыпа́ешься**.",
    "examples": [
      {
        "ru": "У́тром я просыпа́юсь ра́но.",
        "en": "In the morning I wake up early.",
        "note": "-ся stays attached"
      },
      {
        "ru": "Днём я обе́даю.",
        "en": "In the afternoon I have lunch."
      },
      {
        "ru": "Ве́чером я ужина́ю и чита́ю.",
        "en": "In the evening I have dinner and read."
      },
      {
        "ru": "Снача́ла за́втрак, пото́м рабо́та.",
        "en": "First breakfast, then work."
      }
    ]
  },
